A fight over a cooler box on Sunday, 23 May tragically ended the life of a 28-year-old prison warder at a club in Carolina, Mpumalanga. Sizile Sibande was at Mthunzini JunXion when he was assaulted and later shot in the head and chest. Itâ€™s alleged a commotion broke out between Sibande and a bouncer who was denying him access into the club if carrying a cooler box. A Ligwalagwala FM radio presenter was set to perform. Brigadier Leonard Hlathi said the man was taken to hospital, where he was certified dead on arrival. A murder case has been opened and investigations are under way.